Welcome to TEE travels

Your go to travel blog for authentic travel guides and real travel advice.

Hey - I am Tia! A female traveler with a serious case of wanderlust, since my first solo backpacking trip in 2018 I have been addicted to traveling and I am now a full time traveler who is on a mission to explore as much of this world as possible.

Through my first hand experiences from 7+ years of traveling the world I will share with you my unfiltered and honest travel experiences of what it is actually like to travel the world.

With my in-depth travel guides and itineraries, along with my trusted travel resources, I will provide you with everything you need to plan the ultimate travel adventures.​​​​​​​

MY GOAL: to show YOU that no matter the odds, your travel dreams can become a reality. Whether you want to take the leap and make full time travel a reality like me or just plan an amazing holiday or backpacking trip - I am here to teach you how.

To put it simply, Tee Travels is a blog for practical and expert travel advice, along with my personal travel stories - for those of you who have a serious case of wanderlust like ME!

About Me

 

Hello, I'm Tia, and I'm thrilled you've found my blog. If you're a fellow travel enthusiast, you're in the right place. My goal is to explore every country on Earth. Favorites include Montenegro, Guatemala, and Egypt, with dream destinations like Pakistan, Argentina, and Kazakhstan. I've had unforgettable adventures, from volcano boarding to hiking Machu Picchu, but also faced travel challenges. A solo backpacking trip through Southeast Asia kindled my love for budget travel. Despite a health scare and a Crohn's Disease diagnosis in Zambia, I'm committed to exploration. Follow my Instagram for updates on my journeys.
